The Motorcycle Safety Education Commission shall be composed of seven (7) members, appointed as follows:
One (1) representative of the Department of Kentucky State Police, appointed by the Governor;
One (1) representative of the Transportation Cabinet's Division of Driver Licensing, appointed by the Governor;
One (1) instructor in the motorcycle safety education program, appointed by the Governor;
Two (2) members of the Kentucky Motorcycle Association, to be appointed by the Governor from a list of five (5) nominees selected by the association;
One (1) member appointed by the Governor from a list of three (3) nominees selected by the President of the Senate; and
One (1) member appointed by the Governor from a list of three (3) nominees selected by the Speaker of the House of Representatives.
